snippet.textDisplay: That Spider-Man poster is Sony's "kid in the Iron Man mask." it is not MCU Spider-Man until the day it can be MCU Spider-Man. On that day, it will have retroactively been MCU Spider-Man the whole time. And if that day never occursas it did for Peter Parker: kid in the Iron Man mask in the MCU, they can say that it was never MCU Spider-Man in the first place. Plus, Marvel probably owns the specific designs for MCU Spider-Man, forcing Sony to use one of their own, which is fine; they have plenty.
